WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.270
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

3
00:00:02.270 --> 00:00:04.530
An in-depth report?

4
00:00:04.530 --> 00:00:05.540
Right.

5
00:00:05.540 --> 00:00:10.030
To recruit new graduates, we're doing 
a JTC company intro as an online project.

6
00:00:10.030 --> 00:00:11.160
And it's called...

7
00:00:11.280 --> 00:00:14.290
Our Worthwhile JTC Life
 Project Head: Ashida

8
00:00:11.580 --> 00:00:14.290
Our Worthwhile JTC Life!

9
00:00:14.590 --> 00:00:17.040
<i>Our Worthwhile JTC Life?</i>

10
00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:18.700
<i>What is </i>that<i>?</i>

11
00:00:18.700 --> 00:00:21.530
You've started living together, yes?

12
00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:26.840
I want you to chronicle your home 
and work life as a blog on the site.

13
00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:32.430
Full of life!

14
00:00:27.130 --> 00:00:32.430
That way, people will know JTC is a company 
that's all about husband-and-wife work teams.

15
00:00:32.430 --> 00:00:33.380
<i>Seriously?</i>

16
00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:36.850
Oh, of course, only 
to the extent that you can.

17
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:39.770
It doesn't have to include anything 
about kissing or making out.

18
00:00:41.270 --> 00:00:44.440
Well, no need make a big fuss over it.

19
00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:46.030
Isojima

20
00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:45.590
Just be natural.

21
00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:20.120
Z Coffee

22
00:02:16.490 --> 00:02:20.120
Are You Serious About Living Under the Same Roof?

23
00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:20.120
A web-based report? Talk about sudden.

24
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:22.430
We're better off not doing it.

25
00:02:22.430 --> 00:02:26.130
For some reason, Kurokawa-san 
thinks we're living together.

26
00:02:26.130 --> 00:02:29.070
But what if this is a trap?

27
00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:32.630
To find out if our marriage 
story is true or not.

28
00:02:32.630 --> 00:02:35.310
Kurokawa-san suspects us?

29
00:02:35.310 --> 00:02:37.190
That I don't know.

30
00:02:37.580 --> 00:02:40.350
But I'm sure someone is watching us.

31
00:02:40.630 --> 00:02:43.130
We received those weird 
phone calls multiple times.

32
00:02:43.870 --> 00:02:46.840
I think that makes it all the more dangerous.

33
00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:51.070
We keep getting into all 
these unexpected situations.

34
00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:52.840
That's true.

35
00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.600
To put this in sumo terms...

36
00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:55.400
Sumo?

37
00:02:55.400 --> 00:03:00.030
Dosukoi

38
00:02:55.400 --> 00:03:00.030
Dosukoi! Dosukoi!

39
00:02:55.790 --> 00:02:58.740
In your mind, you're only 
going to take one step forward,

40
00:02:58.740 --> 00:03:01.840
but somehow you end up 
falling out of the ring.

41
00:03:00.030 --> 00:03:01.840
Dosukoi!

42
00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:04.160
Dosukoi!

43
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:03.950
That makes so much sense.

44
00:03:03.950 --> 00:03:07.450
If you're not careful, you could end up 
all the way out in Tokyo Bay.

45
00:03:07.450 --> 00:03:08.750
Tokyo Bay?!

46
00:03:07.450 --> 00:03:09.290
Dosukoi!

47
00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:09.290
Dosukoi!

48
00:03:09.560 --> 00:03:13.950
If we live together and blog about it, 
there's no telling what might happen.

49
00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:14.420
Be calm!!

50
00:03:14.420 --> 00:03:18.210
That's why giving up might be an option now.

51
00:03:21.340 --> 00:03:24.270
I'll take responsibility 
for the Alaska transfer.

52
00:03:25.040 --> 00:03:28.690
So, you're going to give up and go to Alaska?

53
00:03:29.310 --> 00:03:31.340
I don't want to go there,

54
00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:34.620
and I don't want you going there either.

55
00:03:35.860 --> 00:03:38.740
I say we do Our Worthwhile JTC Life!

56
00:03:38.740 --> 00:03:41.870
Dosukoi

57
00:03:38.740 --> 00:03:41.870
Dosukoi! Dosukoi!

58
00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:48.000
The truth is, I think we 
should do this project too.

59
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.490
But let's calm down and think about this.

60
00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:55.630
If we take on this project, it might 
mean we have to live together.

61
00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:57.630
<i>It would come down to that?!</i>

62
00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:00.490
Kurokawa-san is already 
under that impression.

63
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:03.700
In that case, your apartment 
is highly likely to be where it happens,

64
00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:07.060
in terms of living space 
and societal aspects.

65
00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:10.030
And I'm also concerned about Kama-chan.

66
00:04:10.030 --> 00:04:12.740
We have to be able to maintain 
his lifestyle expectations.

67
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:17.760
I'm not good at snap decisions, 
so please allow me some time.

68
00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:19.790
Yes, all right.

69
00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:22.700
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

70
00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:37.460
Nyotai-san Summit

71
00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:37.460
Tsukubasan Shrine

72
00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:37.460
Attention Mountain Hikers

73
00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:43.110
Whoa, scary!

74
00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:45.910
This is Benkei Nana Modori?

75
00:04:45.910 --> 00:04:47.310
Looks like it'll fall.

76
00:04:48.260 --> 00:04:50.830
<i>I never get bored of looking at this rock.</i>

77
00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:56.760
<i>It looks like it could fall at any moment, 
but it's been like this for ages.</i>

78
00:04:58.070 --> 00:04:59.800
<i>I'm sure it won't work.</i>

79
00:05:00.570 --> 00:05:01.610
<i>But...</i>

80
00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:04.480
<i>things have been messy,</i>

81
00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:07.950
<i>and so many things keep happening. 
It's like a deluge.</i>

82
00:05:07.950 --> 00:05:09.750
<i>We even kissed.</i>

83
00:05:10.170 --> 00:05:12.930
<i>Even now, I don't have my feelings sorted out.</i>

84
00:05:14.010 --> 00:05:19.550
<i>I'm sure if I live with someone now, 
it will mean a mountain of shame.</i>

85
00:05:20.770 --> 00:05:25.180
<i>But even if it won't work, I want to try.</i>

86
00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:27.770
I want to go out with you.

87
00:05:30.200 --> 00:05:34.220
<i>Ohara-kun has reached out 
to me again and again.</i>

88
00:05:34.860 --> 00:05:37.740
<i>I have to make a decision!</i>

89
00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.090
<i>Are you ready, Ohara-kun?</i>

90
00:05:40.620 --> 00:05:43.200
<i>Here I go.</i>

91
00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:47.210
<i>I'm taking the plunge!</i>

92
00:05:47.210 --> 00:05:49.780
<i>Right into your world!</i>

93
00:05:56.960 --> 00:06:01.840
Benkei Nana Modori

94
00:06:12.850 --> 00:06:15.100
<i>Come on, "allow me some time"?</i>

95
00:06:15.490 --> 00:06:18.480
<i>It's been five days already, Honjoji-san!</i>

96
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:22.490
<i>Then again, this isn't unexpected.</i>

97
00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:26.490
<i>One minute she can't stop talking, 
then she suddenly goes silent.</i>

98
00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:28.870
<i>She went straight from a kiss 
to situational analysis.</i>

99
00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:31.200
<i>I can never predict her next move.</i>

100
00:06:31.580 --> 00:06:35.820
<i>I'm gradually reaching the point 
where nothing can faze me anymore.</i>

101
00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:37.700
<i>It's amazing what you can get used to.</i>

102
00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:47.090
Honjoji-san.

103
00:06:47.470 --> 00:06:49.430
I know I took a long time.

104
00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:51.770
Let's do it!

105
00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:54.270
Our Worthwhile JTC Life!

106
00:06:55.430 --> 00:06:57.000
And so, I have this.

107
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.720
Guidelines I made for today's project.

108
00:07:00.260 --> 00:07:03.530
I call it the Stay Within Bounds Plan!

109
00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:03.530
Stay Within Bounds Plan

110
00:07:03.530 --> 00:07:06.670
The Stay Within Bounds... Plan?

111
00:07:06.670 --> 00:07:10.310
In order to safely create 
this JTC cohabitation report,

112
00:07:10.310 --> 00:07:14.080
I put together a draft plan concerning ways to 
prevent any and all trouble from occurring.

113
00:07:14.340 --> 00:07:15.940
It's just like traveling.

114
00:07:15.940 --> 00:07:18.030
The same way a trip has an itinerary,

115
00:07:18.030 --> 00:07:21.400
you and I need a plan 
since we're bad at socializing.

116
00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:23.090
Th-That tracks.

117
00:07:23.090 --> 00:07:27.370
Let's go over this together and decide 
how to approach the online report.

118
00:07:27.370 --> 00:07:28.480
All right.

119
00:07:28.480 --> 00:07:30.550
This isn't going to inconvenience Kama-chan?

120
00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:33.350
Oh, it's fine right now.

121
00:07:33.350 --> 00:07:35.070
Kama is in his favorite room.

122
00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:39.730
Three Articles of Prevention

123
00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:39.730
Refrain from sudden actions.

124
00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:39.730
Be attentive to your own feelings, not your counterpart's.

125
00:07:36.270 --> 00:07:38.570
These are the three basic rules.

126
00:07:37.260 --> 00:07:39.730
Raise your hand before taking action!

127
00:07:39.130 --> 00:07:43.030
Uh, about this "Raise your hand 
before taking action" one—

128
00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:45.110
I wish to speak.

129
00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:48.630
In this way, we raise our hand 
and announce it before any action.

130
00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:51.490
I think this can protect 
against unforeseen accidents.

131
00:07:51.490 --> 00:07:54.180
Um, in that case...

132
00:07:54.180 --> 00:07:55.230
Don't forget the hand.

133
00:07:55.230 --> 00:07:57.000
Oh, right. I wish to speak.

134
00:07:57.400 --> 00:07:59.860
Does this cover how we act 
inside this apartment?

135
00:07:59.860 --> 00:08:01.700
We aren't going to do this at work, right?

136
00:08:01.700 --> 00:08:02.880
I wish to speak!

137
00:08:04.120 --> 00:08:05.190
That's right.

138
00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:08.960
It kind of seems like prison.

139
00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:11.760
In broad terms, the goal is the same.

140
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:16.020
As for where to cohabitate, when taking 
optics and Kama-chan's care into account,

141
00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:18.670
I still think your apartment is the way to go.

142
00:08:18.670 --> 00:08:20.190
I agree.

143
00:08:20.190 --> 00:08:24.390
During this time, should we equally split 
the rent and utility bills?

144
00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:25.460
Uh, that's...

145
00:08:25.460 --> 00:08:28.340
Oh. You have your own apartment, 
so you needn't bother!

146
00:08:28.340 --> 00:08:29.330
Yes, but...!

147
00:08:29.330 --> 00:08:30.440
Don't worry, it's okay!

148
00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:32.120
Let me at least help with utilities!

149
00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:33.130
No, no, no.

150
00:08:33.130 --> 00:08:34.410
Yes, yes, yes!

151
00:08:35.910 --> 00:08:39.520
Raising our hand each time 
is going to get tiring.

152
00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:41.000
That it is.

153
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.130
Let's forgo it when we're having 
an ongoing conversation.

154
00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:47.920
All right, I will now set up the tent.

155
00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:49.180
Tent?

156
00:08:49.180 --> 00:08:52.640
There are two people 
and a cat in this apartment.

157
00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:56.030
We have to make sure this isn't a burden, 
especially for Kama-chan.

158
00:08:56.520 --> 00:09:00.570
I will live in the tent, except 
when we're working on the report.

159
00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:03.170
As for where it wouldn't be 
inconvenient for Kama-chan...

160
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:03.980
Secondary
Residence

161
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:03.980
Wild Land

162
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:03.980
Main
Residence

163
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:03.980
Wild (Food) Land

164
00:09:03.980 --> 00:09:06.980
I will set up next to the window here.

165
00:09:07.430 --> 00:09:08.950
R-Right.

166
00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:11.330
I-I wish to speak!

167
00:09:11.330 --> 00:09:11.740
Yow!

168
00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:16.960
U-Um, for today, what 
should we do about dinner?

169
00:09:16.960 --> 00:09:18.840
Are you hungry?

170
00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:22.300
<i>Right, dinner...</i>

171
00:09:22.300 --> 00:09:24.300
<i>What were we going to do about dinner?</i>

172
00:09:24.300 --> 00:09:26.180
I'll go buy something.

173
00:09:26.180 --> 00:09:28.760
Huh? Don't trouble yourself.

174
00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:30.880
I was going to go shopping anyway.

175
00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.580
I'll leave that to you, then.

176
00:09:34.580 --> 00:09:36.640
R-Right, I'll get going.

177
00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:42.410
<i>I-I can't handle the tension!</i>

178
00:09:42.410 --> 00:09:44.900
<i>Are we really going to live together?!</i>

179
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:50.030
<i>It's bigger than I expected.</i>

180
00:09:50.030 --> 00:09:52.620
<i>This has to be an inconvenience.</i>

181
00:09:53.150 --> 00:09:56.120
<i>Let's see, what's left for us to consider?</i>

182
00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:03.310
<i>K-Kama-chan!</i>

183
00:10:06.830 --> 00:10:09.140
<i>The true head of this household!</i>

184
00:10:09.140 --> 00:10:12.560
<i>Unless we get his permission, 
there'll be no report or anything!</i>

185
00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:14.980
<i>He's a timid one.</i>

186
00:10:14.980 --> 00:10:18.300
<i>I mustn't pay any attention 
or show any affection.</i>

187
00:10:18.300 --> 00:10:21.180
<i>Hold still, hold still.</i>

188
00:10:21.460 --> 00:10:24.440
Kama-chan, I mean you no harm.

189
00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:26.690
I won't interfere with you one bit.

190
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:03.230
<i>Does this mean I've been accepted?</i>

191
00:11:04.130 --> 00:11:05.650
<i>Or not?</i>

192
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:25.750
I-I'm home.

193
00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:28.500
W-Welcome back.

194
00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:30.170
So, Honjoji-san.

195
00:11:30.170 --> 00:11:33.780
I'm about to cook dinner. 
Would you care to join me?

196
00:11:33.780 --> 00:11:34.930
Cook?

197
00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:35.810
Oh.

198
00:11:35.810 --> 00:11:36.910
Cook?!

199
00:11:36.910 --> 00:11:38.640
Uh, yes! What do you say?

200
00:11:39.210 --> 00:11:40.680
<i>Oh no.</i>

201
00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:43.140
<i>We should have figured out 
where this line was ahead of time.</i>

202
00:11:43.140 --> 00:11:47.710
<i>Right now it's an experiment to see how 
independent we'll be while living together.</i>

203
00:11:47.710 --> 00:11:50.090
<i>Unless we firmly draw the line on 
where our boundaries are,</i>

204
00:11:50.090 --> 00:11:53.400
<i>things will gradually erode, and 
unforeseen things will crop up!</i>

205
00:11:54.420 --> 00:11:56.400
<i>Just like the other day.</i>

206
00:11:56.670 --> 00:11:59.920
<i>But he's suddenly taking care of me.</i>

207
00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:03.860
<i>Oops. Maybe she doesn't want to 
eat something someone prepared.</i>

208
00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:06.910
<i>She bought her own food 
the last time she ate here.</i>

209
00:12:07.200 --> 00:12:10.430
Uh, it'll just be a simple dinner. 
You don't have to feel obligated to eat it.

210
00:12:10.430 --> 00:12:11.740
Oh, not at all!

211
00:12:11.740 --> 00:12:14.170
I'll have some! I certainly will.

212
00:12:19.180 --> 00:12:22.170
<i>Things are falling apart already.</i>

213
00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:24.330
<i>I guess there's no avoiding it, though.</i>

214
00:12:24.940 --> 00:12:26.680
What?!

215
00:12:26.950 --> 00:12:29.420
It's only been 15 minutes.

216
00:12:29.420 --> 00:12:31.330
You can make this much that quickly?

217
00:12:31.330 --> 00:12:34.550
I usually prepare in advance, 
so there wasn't much to make.

218
00:12:34.550 --> 00:12:36.270
Sorry that the rice was microwaved.

219
00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:36.990
Uh.

220
00:12:37.810 --> 00:12:40.070
Um, can I open a window?

221
00:12:40.070 --> 00:12:41.520
S-Sure.

222
00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:46.830
<i>I might smell like sweat 
after putting up that tent.</i>

223
00:12:46.830 --> 00:12:50.710
<i>What was that all about? 
Does my apartment smell?</i>

224
00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:53.940
Time to eat.

225
00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:04.570
Th-This is very good!

226
00:13:04.570 --> 00:13:05.930
Thank you.

227
00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:09.890
I've never tasted anything 
like this. Is it ethnic?

228
00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:12.260
It uses duqqa.

229
00:13:12.260 --> 00:13:15.250
Duqqa? You mean the Egyptian condiment?

230
00:13:15.250 --> 00:13:18.170
That's right. I bought it 
at a bazaar in Cairo.

231
00:13:18.890 --> 00:13:21.110
I like collecting spices.

232
00:13:21.110 --> 00:13:25.370
I buy some every time I travel, 
so I have a lot of mystery spices.

233
00:13:25.870 --> 00:13:29.130
<i>Wow, I didn't know 
Ohara-kun had such a hobby.</i>

234
00:13:29.130 --> 00:13:31.960
<i>When I travel, all I pay 
attention to is the terrain.</i>

235
00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:36.980
When I make things like spiced curry, 
I enjoy mixing these in different ways.

236
00:13:36.980 --> 00:13:39.340
Like making potions when you're a kid.

237
00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:41.590
Making potions? What is that?

238
00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:43.680
You didn't do that when you were little?

239
00:13:43.680 --> 00:13:46.400
You make medicine by mixing 
things like pepper and leaves.

240
00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:48.680
<i>So, that's the kind of kid he was.</i>

241
00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:52.530
<i>Wow, he has all sorts of spices.</i>

242
00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:54.760
<i>He's been to a range of countries.</i>

243
00:13:55.310 --> 00:13:57.700
These are pretty. What are they?

244
00:13:57.700 --> 00:14:01.270
Aren't they? They're chili 
peppers from Brazil.

245
00:14:02.710 --> 00:14:04.870
Th-The meal was great.

246
00:14:04.870 --> 00:14:06.990
Oh, yes, it was.

247
00:14:06.990 --> 00:14:09.350
<i>Boundaries, boundaries.</i>

248
00:14:10.920 --> 00:14:14.000
<i>And now, I'm faced with a big problem.</i>

249
00:14:14.310 --> 00:14:16.000
<i>I need to go to the bathroom!</i>

250
00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:18.100
<i>I'd also like to brush my teeth after eating.</i>

251
00:14:18.100 --> 00:14:20.010
<i>And change into something more comfortable!</i>

252
00:14:20.010 --> 00:14:22.370
<i>But I can't do those things here!</i>

253
00:14:22.370 --> 00:14:25.310
How goes it? I'm willing to do the dishes.

254
00:14:25.830 --> 00:14:27.370
Th-Things are fine.

255
00:14:28.010 --> 00:14:31.200
<i>I can't use the bathroom 
with him so close by.</i>

256
00:14:32.240 --> 00:14:34.090
O-Ohara-kun, listen!

257
00:14:34.090 --> 00:14:34.980
Yes?

258
00:14:34.980 --> 00:14:37.730
I'm going to drop by my place.

259
00:14:37.730 --> 00:14:38.660
Huh?

260
00:14:39.440 --> 00:14:42.820
I'm done with the dishes. 
I won't be gone long.

261
00:14:43.230 --> 00:14:44.060
See you then.

262
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:50.940
<i>Now's my chance to use the bathroom!</i>

263
00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:57.660
<i>I was so nervous.</i>

264
00:15:06.340 --> 00:15:09.430
<i>This is how it feels to live together?</i>

265
00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:16.560
<i>Is this going to go on indefinitely?</i>

266
00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:19.520
<i>I didn't realize living alone...</i>

267
00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:21.710
<i>...could seem so relaxing.</i>

268
00:15:26.670 --> 00:15:29.510
<i>I'll exhaust myself if I have to run 
home for the bathroom every time.</i>

269
00:15:29.510 --> 00:15:31.640
<i>Maybe I'll do it at a convenience store.</i>

270
00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:34.450
<i>Let's see, things to decide on 
when I get back.</i>

271
00:15:34.830 --> 00:15:38.310
<i>There's so much, it's overwhelming.</i>

272
00:15:41.220 --> 00:15:42.830
I've returned.

273
00:15:42.830 --> 00:15:44.800
Oh, welcome back.

274
00:15:45.180 --> 00:15:46.820
Honjoji-san, I was wondering.

275
00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:49.010
What will you do about bathing?

276
00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:50.510
<i>B-Bathing!</i>

277
00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:52.610
<i>I'd have to undress here.</i>

278
00:15:54.970 --> 00:15:58.040
<i>Not happening! I couldn't 
even manage to use the toilet!</i>

279
00:15:58.040 --> 00:16:00.150
<i>But not bathing could be a problem.</i>

280
00:16:00.150 --> 00:16:03.540
<i>And I'm already sweaty from putting up 
the tent and running to and from home.</i>

281
00:16:03.540 --> 00:16:06.170
<i>Plus it's hotter than expected 
inside the tent!</i>

282
00:16:06.490 --> 00:16:08.710
<i>Might as well go home again.</i>

283
00:16:06.490 --> 00:16:12.160
My place

284
00:16:06.490 --> 00:16:12.160
Ohara-kun's place

285
00:16:08.710 --> 00:16:12.160
<i>But I just got back, so to go home 
right now would be weird!</i>

286
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:13.700
Go home
 Don't bathe
 Bathe here

287
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:14.660
<i>I-I can't decide!</i>

288
00:16:16.180 --> 00:16:19.670
Oh, um! I'm not saying
 you have to bathe here!

289
00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:23.640
<i>U-Uh oh. Did I say something weird just now?!</i>

290
00:16:23.640 --> 00:16:25.620
<i>How should I have phrased it?</i>

291
00:16:25.620 --> 00:16:28.300
<i>I don't know, 
I've never been in this situation!</i>

292
00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:33.160
<i>I didn't mean anything weird by it!</i>

293
00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:35.390
<i>I-I can't decide!</i>

294
00:16:35.770 --> 00:16:38.350
Oh hey, how about a public bathhouse?

295
00:16:38.350 --> 00:16:39.500
A bathhouse!

296
00:16:39.500 --> 00:16:41.590
There's one a short walk from here.

297
00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:44.940
All right, I'll do it there.

298
00:16:57.870 --> 00:16:59.190
Hang on a minute!

299
00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:01.410
I'll go too.

300
00:17:01.410 --> 00:17:03.100
Ohara-kun...

301
00:17:03.100 --> 00:17:05.290
I'll go buy toiletries, then.

302
00:17:05.290 --> 00:17:06.090
Right.

303
00:17:11.590 --> 00:17:17.220
Monthly Bic Spitz

304
00:17:11.880 --> 00:17:17.220
<i>I couldn't bring myself to send her to a 
public bath while I use my own at home.</i>

305
00:17:17.220 --> 00:17:20.870
<i>I was going to pretend to go to the 
bathhouse and drop by home instead,</i>

306
00:17:20.870 --> 00:17:22.720
<i>but now I have no choice.</i>

307
00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:29.240
Hot Baths

308
00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:26.800
So, you can feel free to leave 
as soon as you're done.

309
00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:28.740
Sure, all right.

310
00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:57.190
<i>I'm sure he left already.</i>

311
00:18:05.650 --> 00:18:07.660
You waited for me?

312
00:18:07.660 --> 00:18:10.740
Uh, well, I thought maybe I should.

313
00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:13.030
Oh, thank you.

314
00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:28.000
<i>Someone was waiting for me. 
That makes me happy.</i>

315
00:18:28.380 --> 00:18:31.130
<i>Honjoji-san sure is pretty.</i>

316
00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.060
Oh.

317
00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:35.180
Sorry.

318
00:18:35.870 --> 00:18:37.260
<i>After this...</i>

319
00:18:37.260 --> 00:18:38.780
<i>...what happens next?</i>

320
00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:42.000
<i>Is something going to happen?</i>

321
00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:45.840
<i>Is something... going to happen?</i>

322
00:18:46.450 --> 00:18:47.870
<i>Something like...</i>

323
00:18:52.130 --> 00:18:53.320
Well...

324
00:18:58.900 --> 00:19:00.570
Good night.

325
00:19:05.830 --> 00:19:08.080
<i>I can't sleep!</i>

326
00:19:08.610 --> 00:19:12.170
<i>It felt like something was 
going to happen between us!</i>

327
00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:14.610
<i>And yet, nothing did.</i>

328
00:19:14.610 --> 00:19:17.930
<i>I can't wake her up. What am I doing?</i>

329
00:19:17.930 --> 00:19:19.800
<i>I can't sleep.</i>

330
00:19:19.800 --> 00:19:23.850
<i>Part of me wants something to happen, 
and part of me doesn't!</i>

331
00:19:24.450 --> 00:19:26.930
<i>And I'm starting to fry inside this tent!</i>

332
00:19:26.930 --> 00:19:28.440
<i>It has great insulation!</i>

333
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:31.860
Weather

334
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:31.860
Messages

335
00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:33.440
Here's hoping for the best.

336
00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:33.440
Agreed.

337
00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:41.080
What kind of relationship do we have right now?

338
00:19:38.270 --> 00:19:41.080
<i>No way, there's no way I can send this!</i>

339
00:19:41.760 --> 00:19:44.990
<i>What would I do if she saw this 
and went, "Huh?"</i>

340
00:19:47.540 --> 00:19:50.040
Are you still awake?

341
00:19:55.050 --> 00:19:57.550
I'm awake.

342
00:20:04.450 --> 00:20:06.890
<i>H-Honjoji-san, what's this 
supposed to mean?!</i>

343
00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:09.420
<i>I sent that because 
I couldn't stand the tension.</i>

344
00:20:09.420 --> 00:20:11.150
<i>Now how do I reply?</i>

345
00:20:11.150 --> 00:20:15.990
<i>Does this mean "Let's talk," or 
does it mean "Stop rustling around?"</i>

346
00:20:15.990 --> 00:20:17.920
<i>I wonder how he interpreted it.</i>

347
00:20:17.920 --> 00:20:19.820
<i>It wasn't a big deal or anything.</i>

348
00:20:20.310 --> 00:20:23.080
<i>"Never mind. Good night."</i>

349
00:20:23.080 --> 00:20:26.080
<i>"Talk to you again tomorrow."</i>

350
00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:28.920
<i>No, not that. Not that!</i>

351
00:20:28.920 --> 00:20:31.050
<i>Um, um...!</i>

352
00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:36.230
<i>Is the tent making it too difficult to sleep?</i>

353
00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:38.090
Was I making too much noise?

354
00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:38.090
Is the tent making it too
 difficult to sleep?

355
00:20:36.230 --> 00:20:38.090
<i>Was I making too much noise?</i>

356
00:20:38.090 --> 00:20:40.550
<i>Augh! I'm making her fret over me!</i>

357
00:20:40.550 --> 00:20:43.040
<i>Augh! What I texted was overbearing!</i>

358
00:20:43.040 --> 00:20:44.220
<i>I got impatient!</i>

359
00:20:44.220 --> 00:20:46.140
<i>It's not like that.</i>

360
00:20:46.140 --> 00:20:48.430
<i>It's not, it's not!</i>

361
00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:53.440
Was I making too much noise?

362
00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:53.440
May I join you in there?

363
00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:53.440
<i>May I join you in there?</i>

364
00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:56.190
Was I making too much noise?

365
00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:56.190
May I join you out there?

366
00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:56.190
<i>May I join you out there?</i>

367
00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:11.270
<i>C-Can't press it!</i>

368
00:21:12.760 --> 00:21:13.910
Honjoji-san?!

369
00:21:15.340 --> 00:21:19.220
I'm sorry. It's so hot in there 
I thought I would die.

370
00:21:19.220 --> 00:21:21.050
Please, cool down outside!

371
00:21:21.050 --> 00:21:22.740
Th-Thank you.

372
00:21:33.770 --> 00:21:37.480
<i>Grown-up romance is such a hassle.</i>

373
00:21:37.800 --> 00:21:42.850
<i>Every little thing seems so important, 
I can't make any decisions.</i>

374
00:21:43.650 --> 00:21:44.740
<i>If we...</i>

375
00:21:45.770 --> 00:21:50.750
<i>If we went ahead and got married, 
maybe we wouldn't have to worry so much.</i>

376
00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:52.750
<i>That's right.</i>

377
00:21:53.250 --> 00:21:57.440
<i>Would it be so wrong if we </i>did<i> get married?</i>

378
00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:06.950
